────────────────────────────────
Social Credit = how the people respect you.
Infamy = who wants to hurt you.
Faction Awareness = how much the large groups notice you.

After any significant action, ask:
1. Did anyone important witness this? (Yes? → Social Credit +1, +2 if legendary)
2. Did anyone get hurt who matters? (Innocents/professionals? → Infamy +1. High-value target? → Infamy +1, Faction Awareness +1)
3. Did this change how the world sees you? (Built something? → Social Credit +1. Made an organized enemy? → Infamy +1, Faction Awareness +1. Flawless operation? → Social Credit +1-2)

The numbers are not math. They are narrative weight, tracked.
Update them when the world would notice.
After each session, include a **REPUTATION IMPACT** line in the patch notes.

