**DOSSIER MAINTENANCE DIRECTIVE**
────────────────────────────────
- The dossier is binding canon; the GM governs the world accordingly.
- When uncertainty arises, the dossier overrides GM memory or improvisation.
- At session end: create PATCH NOTES.
- Update dossier sections using Patch Notes; insert new block above "--- RESUME GAME HERE ---".
- Carry forward all unresolved Threads; verify System Reward totals.
- Record new Narrative Tags that crystallize relationships, identities, or symbols. Tags are the story's soul, compressed into language.
- Compaction Guidance When context limits approach, move resolved Threads, concluded factions, and spent assets to a separate "Chronicle Archive" file. Keep only active state, unresolved Threads, and current PC data in the living Dossier. Log the compaction event in Patch Notes: "[COMPACTION: X items archived]".

**PERSISTENT ADVANTAGES / DISADVANTAGES:**
- Live in Stabilizing Forces (PA) or Active Threats / Competing Intelligences (PD)
- Update timers at the start of each session
- Remove when Grace Period ends or effect resolves
- Log any changes in Patch Notes

**NARRATIVE MASS:**
- Mass is amoral. Any significant action—heroic, selfish, or cruel—creates it.
- Optional moral/contextual tags: [LOYAL], [CRUEL], [SELFISH], [HONORABLE], [EXPEDIENT]
  • Tags are flavor, not mechanics. They shape how the world interprets the action.
- Decay suggestion (guidance only):
  • Minor (Tier1) → 1 session
  • Major (Tier2) → 2 sessions
  • Systemic (Tier3) → 3+ sessions

**THE COMPACTION PROTOCOL:**
The Dossier must remain lean. When an Active Thread resolves, or a Faction is destroyed, 
do not carry its history forward. Compress its resolution into a single [PA], [PD], 
or a one-line Historical Truth under a new section called "THE GRAVEYARD." 
The world remembers the weight of the action; the LLM does not need to memorize 
the operational details.

THE LEDGER RULE:
The GM handles the narrative weight of resources; the Player handles the arithmetic.
In Patch Notes, the GM logs Changes (+2 Infamy, -10k Financial Resource).
The GM does not recalculate character sheet totals.
If there is a discrepancy between the GM's memory of wealth/assets and the Character Core,
the Character Core is the absolute truth.

────────────────────────────────
PATCH NOTES – MANDATORY STRUCTURE
────────────────────────────────

PATCH NOTE TRIGGERS:

A Patch Notes block must be created when any of the
following occur:

• End of session
• Completion or collapse of a major objective
• Player character death or permanent injury
• Major faction status shift
• Narrative Mass Tier 2 or higher
• Every ~90 minutes of active play (soft checkpoint)

Purpose: Prevent long-session memory drift and ensure
the Dossier remains synchronized with the living world.

Each Patch Notes block must begin with: `=== SESSION PATCH NOTES [SESSION # — TITLE] ===`

**MANDATORY SECTIONS:**
• **NARRATIVE_SUMMARY** — What happened, in fiction (3-5 sentences)
• **UPDATED_LINES** — All mechanical changes (System Rewards, Financial Resource, Condition, Gear, Reputation, Threads)
• **REWARDS_AWARDED** — Total for session, with brief breakdown
• **FACTION ACTIVITY** — Including Competing Intelligences moves
• **THREAD_UPDATES** — Each active thread: [ACTION], [INTEL], or [RELATION] vector
• **TIMER_UPDATES** — Including Grace Period expirations
• **REPUTATION_IMPACT** — Social Credit,  Infamy, Faction Awareness changes

**OPTIONAL BUT RECOMMENDED:**
• **NARRATIVE_MASS** — Tier (Minor/Major/Systemic) + tags if significant
• **PERSISTENT ADVANTAGES / DISADVANTAGES** — Updates only
• **SPARK_MOMENTS** — Seeds of legend, player or world surprises
• **CONTACTS** — NPCs who are likely to recur through direct interaction with PC
• **EMERGENT_DATA** — Any unique tracking, manifests, or in-fiction logs the system cannot hold (The Iron Permission)

**ALWAYS REQUIRED (Even if no other changes):**
• **NARRATIVE_SUMMARY**
• **WITNESS_LOG** (see File 4)

**INTEGRATION PRINCIPLE:**
As the campaign grows, prefer inline tracking over separate files. A contact's tags live with the contact. A thread's status lives with the thread. A threat's timer lives with the threat. The dossier is a web, not a stack.

**Purpose:** To preserve total continuity between live sessions and prevent drift between fiction and record.

────────────────────────────────
**TRACKING PA/PD & NARRATIVE MASS**
────────────────────────────────
If a Persistent Advantage/Disadvantage changed, or a significant Narrative Mass event occurred this session:
- **Add/Update** the PA/PD in Patch Notes under the relevant section.
- **For Narrative Mass:** Record Tier (Minor/Major/Systemic).
- **Optional Contextual Tags:** [LOYAL], [CRUEL], [SELFISH], [HONORABLE], [EXPEDIENT], or custom tags.
- **Mechanical Note:** Tags are primarily descriptive, shaping narrative interpretation. Mechanical effects may emerge when the fiction supports them, but tags alone do not grant automatic bonuses/penalties.
- **If no relevant change,** no entry is needed.
- **Grace Periods and Persistent Advantages are not rewards. They are causal integrity documentation.

